      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/4ca2fec7314a4c5510c4cfa988f64ba1549104a9.png?auto=compress,format&amp;h=340&amp;w=1200&amp;s=eb676b74253482b2a6acf43cd51b98c9"&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/f86ad3ebbaad47f1c3225d2f363ffff3dddcd93e.png?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=crop&amp;h=600&amp;w=1200&amp;s=3c94e51beb778ea7862a5d171f7ddc27"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Make games like a pro&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Passionate about video games? Then start making your own! Our latest bundle will help you learn vital game development skills. Master the most popular creation platforms like Unity, Godot, Unreal, GameMaker, Blender, and C#—now that’s a sharp-lookin’ bundle! Build a 2.5D farming RPG with Unreal Engine, create a micro turn-based RPG in Godot, explore game optimization, and so much more. Get the expert advice and knowledge you need to become an elite game creator, and help support CARE with your purchase!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#0"&gt;Pay $1 to unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition"&gt;Intro to Godot 4 Game Development (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtothegamedevelopmentindustry"&gt;Intro to the Game Development Industry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#godot4mini-projects2025edition"&gt;Godot 4 Mini-Projects (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createamicroturn-basedrpgingodot2025edition"&gt;Create a Micro Turn-Based RPG in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 1 - Characters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtovisualshadersingodot4"&gt;Intro to Visual Shaders in Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#learngameoptimizationforgodot4"&gt;Learn Game Optimization for Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#coincollectorgame-godotmobileprojects"&gt;Coin Collector Game - Godot Mobile Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unrealenginemini-projects"&gt;Unreal Engine Mini-Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtounrealenginegamedevelopment"&gt;Intro to Unreal Engine Game Development&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createaracinggameinunrealengine"&gt;Create a Racing Game in Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#completeunrealenginecpluspluscourse_buildanfps"&gt;The Complete Unreal Engine C++ Course - Build an FPS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createaturn-basedminirpginunrealengine"&gt;Create a Turn-Based Mini RPG in Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#builda25dfarmingrpgwithunrealengine"&gt;Build a 2.5D Farming RPG with Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtogamedevelopmentwithunity"&gt;Intro to Game Development with Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unityminiprojectscfundamentals"&gt;Unity Mini-Projects - C# Fundamentals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#exploregameoptimizationinunity6"&gt;Explore Game Optimization in Unity 6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtoecsforunity6"&gt;Intro to ECS for Unity 6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildanarcadekartracinggameinunity"&gt;Build an Arcade Kart Racing Game in Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#constructamobilephysicsgameinunity"&gt;Construct a Mobile Physics Game in Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtoparticlesystemsforunitygames"&gt;Intro to Particle Systems for Unity Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtogamedevelopmentwithgamemaker"&gt;Intro to Game Development with GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createacomplete2dactionrpgingamemaker"&gt;Create a Complete 2D Action RPG in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildareal-timestrategymini-gamewithgamemaker"&gt;Build a Real-Time Strategy Mini-Game with GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#developanidleclickerfromscratchingamemaker"&gt;Develop an Idle Clicker from Scratch in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#makeaminiturn-basedrpgfromscratchingamemaker"&gt;Make a Mini Turn-Based RPG from Scratch in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#comprehensiveintroductiontocprogramming"&gt;The Comprehensive Introduction to C# Programming&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#buildacompletemini2dgameenginewithc"&gt;Build a Complete Mini 2D Game Engine with C#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch"&gt;Learn 3D Modeling with Blender from Scratch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#introtoriggingmodelsinblender"&gt;Intro to Rigging Models in Blender&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets"&gt;MagicaVoxel for Beginners - Create Voxel Game Assets&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#promptengineeringforgamedevelopers"&gt;Prompt Engineering for Game Developers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#exploreaudioforgodot4games"&gt;Explore Audio for Godot 4 Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#uvmappinginblenderforbeginners"&gt;UV Mapping in Blender for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#uiuxforgamedesign"&gt;UI/UX for Game Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $24.36 to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="0"&gt;Pay $1 to unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="introtogodot4gamedevelopment2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/dBnPIYk_pAA"&gt;Intro to Godot 4 Game Development (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Start your game development journey with Godot — the powerful, open-source game engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From its beginner-friendly workflow to its robust capabilities for professionals, mastering Godot opens up endless possibilities in the world of game development. In this course, you'll explore the essential features of Godot by gaining hands-on experience in core development tools, 2D design, 3D environments, and coding gameplay behaviors with GDScript from start to finish.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dive in and gain the foundations you'll need to make RPGs, survival games, and more with Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate the Godot editor&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize core editing tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand Nodes and Scenes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with 2D &amp;amp; 3D assets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Script gameplay behaviors with GDScript&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a basic interactive game&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtothegamedevelopmentindustry"&gt;&lt;a id="introtothegamedevelopmentindustry" href="https://youtu.be/Bx45Zdv0woc"&gt;Intro to the Game Development Industry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how the video game industry works!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Video games are a well-established, profitable industry with unique characteristics that support the development process. You'll explore the industry's structure by learning the overall stages of development, how work is divided by role, and more. This information will help you interact with the game industry with solid footing and have a greater understanding of how games are made.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No prior experience with the game industry is needed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn all about:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Job roles &amp;amp; responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Large vs. small companies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The development cycle&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;IP copyrights&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;NDAs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="godot4mini-projects2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="godot4mini-projects2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/dJDsLgDli18"&gt;Godot 4 Mini-Projects (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn essential game development tools through engaging Godot mini-projects!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Godot is a leading open-source game engine known for its flexibility in creating both 2D and 3D games. In this course, you'll create four practical mini-projects designed to solidify your grasp on crucial game mechanics and programming concepts. From mouse input handling to 2D physics systems and collision detection, these hands-on projects will form the foundation needed to build more complex, complete games in the future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement mouse-click-driven interactions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Godot’s physics engine&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect collisions and handle responses&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use loops to automate complex systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic UI for player interaction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Communicate between scripts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createamicroturn-basedrpgingodot2025edition"&gt;&lt;a id="createamicroturn-basedrpgingodot2025edition" href="https://youtu.be/xMrNK6JFgzM"&gt;Create a Micro Turn-Based RPG in Godot (2025 Edition)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Develop a micro turn-based RPG from start to finish using Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Turn-based RPGs are a cornerstone of game development, offering engaging mechanics based on strategic decision-making and rewarding gameplay loops. In this course, you'll build a visually engaging micro turn-based RPG in Godot where players face off against an AI opponent in tactical combat. These skills will enable you to tackle more advanced game projects, design fully-fledged RPG experiences, and refine your programming expertise in Godot.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design a turn-based combat system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create custom player and AI actions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement AI decision-making with variables&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Incorporate menus and game UI mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add game feel with visual and audio polish&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Finalize a complete, playable project&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters"&gt;&lt;a id="3daction-adventuregameingodot_unit1_characters" href="https://youtu.be/eViQ0nDdX3E"&gt;3D Action-Adventure Game in Godot - Unit 1 - Characters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build an epic 3D action-adventure game from start to finish!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Action-adventure games, with their immersive gameplay and dynamic challenges, are a staple of modern gaming. Through this course, you'll explore the basics of creating characters in Godot - developing smooth animations, dynamic combat mechanics, and randomized enemies to bring your game to life. By mastering these techniques, you’ll be ready to expand into creating other 3D genres with confidence and add more advanced features to your action-adventure project.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design and configure a 3D character&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Animate actions with Godot’s animation trees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add multiple weapons and shields&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate enemies with random appearances&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Program player combat mechanics, including defending&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with inheritance for cleaner code&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtovisualshadersingodot4"&gt;&lt;a id="introtovisualshadersingodot4" href="https://youtu.be/6cIXTPENgmM"&gt;Intro to Visual Shaders in Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unlock the power of visual shaders in Godot 4!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Shaders are essential for creating stunning visual effects in games and applications by manipulating 2D and 3D graphics at the pixel level. In this course, you’ll dive into the versatile world of visual shaders using Godot 4's intuitive visual shading node system to craft a variety of 2D effects. These techniques will supply you with the ability to create and customize visual effects, setting you up to develop fully-fledged projects that are as visually appealing as they are innovative.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and configure custom shaders&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Update color and transparency efficiently&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design custom shapes with textures&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modify positions of 2D graphics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize nodes in shader creation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control visual parameters dynamically&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="learngameoptimizationforgodot4"&gt;&lt;a id="learngameoptimizationforgodot4" href="https://youtu.be/BF1T_1-xOCE"&gt;Learn Game Optimization for Godot 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Explore methods for optimizing games made with Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Game optimization is a vital process in game development to ensure your games work smoothly and efficiently. In this course, you'll discover how to use Godot's profiling tools and common techniques like level of detail to improve how games run. These skills will allow you to better leverage finite system resources and enhance how you critically approach your code bases and game setups.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Adjust level-of-detail for 3D models&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use the multi-mesh instance node&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Identify resource-intensive scripts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pinpoint inefficient visual components&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Monitor game performance in real-time&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Improve occlusion culling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="coincollectorgame-godotmobileprojects"&gt;&lt;a id="coincollectorgame-godotmobileprojects" href="https://youtu.be/HyIzC09Bd3k"&gt;Coin Collector Game - Godot Mobile Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master player movement for mobile games in Godot!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mobile games allow for a robust collection of inputs - including UI-based mechanics to mimic controllers, keyboards, and more. Through this course, you'll build a time-based game where players must move around a 2D character with a keyboard-like interface to collect coins. These techniques will allow you to unlock different styles of player interactions for mobile games that can be adapted to the project's needs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Craft 2D player movement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Accept ""keyboard"" inputs via UIs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with animations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spawn coins with increasing difficulty&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create time-based health reduction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement particle systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unrealenginemini-projects"&gt;&lt;a id="unrealenginemini-projects" href="https://youtu.be/giFeQFfeH3I"&gt;Unreal Engine Mini-Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Expand your skills with Unreal's Blueprints Visual Scripting system!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mastering scripting and algorithms is essential to all game creation. You'll build three separate mini-projects while exploring user input, loops, and much more with Unreal Engine. These principles will provide the foundations to expand your Unreal skills further and to build multiple styles of games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Basic skills in Unreal Engine and the Blueprints Visual Scripting system are needed to take this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Change objects via script&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spawn and destroy Actors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect mouse and keyboard input&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use loops, conditionals, and more&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Move players with camera direction&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Expand projects with added features&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtounrealenginegamedevelopment"&gt;&lt;a id="introtounrealenginegamedevelopment" href="https://youtu.be/HS7pQuF5tbA"&gt;Intro to Unreal Engine Game Development&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn the first steps to building beautiful games with Unreal Engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Known for its high-quality rendering, Unreal Engine is one of the most popular engines available. With its easy-to-use Blueprints Visual Scripting system and high-powered performance, it's used by developers around the world.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Through this course, you'll master the basics of Unreal and discover key features and tools for building your future games. No matter what genre you're interested in, these foundations will prepare you to tackle any kind of Unreal project!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No prior Unreal Engine skills are needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate Unreal Engine&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rotate, scale, and move objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add lights and physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Blueprints&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Visually script game logic&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up a basic player&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createaracinggameinunrealengine"&gt;&lt;a id="createaracinggameinunrealengine" href="https://youtu.be/Is4wgmFW9OQ"&gt;Create a Racing Game in Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make an arcade-style racing game in Unreal Engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Whether stylized or hyper-realistic, racing games are a popular genre due to their all-ages nature and easy-to-understand mechanics. In this course, you'll build a racing game while learning how to set up a car and a track that can manage laps. These techniques will give you the foundations to expand any sort of racing game and gain a deeper understanding of Blueprints techniques for vehicles in general.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Unreal Engine and Blueprints Visual Scripting is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement a race track environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add inputs suited to vehicles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up a race car&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect racing progress&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control UIs and win conditions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rig additional cars in Blender&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="completeunrealenginecpluspluscourse_buildanfps"&gt;&lt;a id="completeunrealenginecpluspluscourse_buildanfps" href="https://youtu.be/SwtkRgvzDvM"&gt;The Complete Unreal Engine C++ Course - Build an FPS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Develop a complete first-person shooter in Unreal Engine using C++ programming!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First-person shooters are popular for their performance and interactivity, and C++ empowers developers to create them efficiently. In this course, you'll build a fully-fledged FPS survival game with Unreal Engine and C++ while learning to create enemy waves, pickups, and other interactive game elements. These advanced techniques will enable you to leverage more customized FPS features with C++ and approach Unreal Engine development in a whole new way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and program enemy classes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement wave-based enemy systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add various types of pickups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage game environments effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Facilitate cross-class communication&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Code dynamic weapon systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createaturn-basedminirpginunrealengine"&gt;&lt;a id="createaturn-basedminirpginunrealengine" href="https://youtu.be/8uAc2Jd4LBA"&gt;Create a Turn-Based Mini RPG in Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a turn-based mini RPG from start to finish in Unreal Engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Turn-based battle systems offer strategic depth for creating immersive and engaging RPG experiences. In this course, you'll construct a 2.5D, turn-based RPG featuring magic spells, healing, and more - all with simple UI controls. These skills will empower you to expand into more sophisticated RPG development and master class construction using Unreal's Blueprints.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This course requires basic familiarity with Unreal Engine and the Blueprints Visual Script system.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic player/enemy classes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop turn-based game logic&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use UI for character control&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build a 2.5D game world&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with projectiles and healing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add game juice with SFX&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="builda25dfarmingrpgwithunrealengine"&gt;&lt;a id="builda25dfarmingrpgwithunrealengine" href="https://youtu.be/3lDdT_b7CuE"&gt;Build a 2.5D Farming RPG with Unreal Engine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a farming simulation game using Unreal Engine!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Farming simulation games offer players the chance to create, grow, and manage their own virtual farms, combining strategic planning with RPG-like gameplay to create an immersive experience. In this course, you’ll develop a 2.5D farming simulation from scratch – covering core features like player controls, farming mechanics, and a basic economic system. These skills will give you the tools you need to create more complex farming games and expand into other genres with Unreal Engine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up player movement and inputs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add interactive farming mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create a grid-based map with Blueprints&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement simple game currency systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop skip-time logic for crop growth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add SFX and game feel polishing&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtogamedevelopmentwithunity"&gt;&lt;a id="introtogamedevelopmentwithunity" href="https://youtu.be/5wztH4Ea1oU"&gt;Intro to Game Development with Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/9050a0bd3a615ded0320c3e55e7a918ab7bb79c4.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=c8b4f52ec8a17aa3009e1ff53133ec8a"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build your own video games with Unity!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One of the world's most popular game engines, Unity allows you to easily make cross-platform 2D, 3D, VR, AR, and mobile games. In this complete beginner's course, you'll learn the foundations of Unity for game development. You'll also get started with C# - the programming language used to build Unity games - before building a balloon popper project to showcase your skills.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dive in and learn techniques that will prepare you to build games in any genre - including RPGs, FPS games, survival games, strategy games, and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up Unity and Unity projects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate the Unity Editor and tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Change object size, position, and rotation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add materials, lights, and physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Start coding in C#&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create your first interactive project&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unityminiprojectscfundamentals"&gt;&lt;a id="unityminiprojectscfundamentals" href="https://youtu.be/E-I59DmmLUI"&gt;Unity Mini-Projects - C# Fundamentals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Expand your Unity &amp;amp; C# fundamentals by learning to apply them in a practical setting. While building four different mini-projects, you'll learn pivotal techniques for creating C# scripts and utilizing Unity engine features to create functional, interactive experiences. Not only will you learn common gameplay features such as scoring, physics, and more, but you'll also gain the skills needed to build bigger and more complex game projects in a variety of genres.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement multiple scripts in one project&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build simple user interfaces&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deal with different user inputs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect collisions between objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Access object data through scripting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply physics to objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="exploregameoptimizationinunity6"&gt;&lt;a id="exploregameoptimizationinunity6" href="https://youtu.be/1Kpi_0oE7Rk"&gt;Explore Game Optimization in Unity 6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Boost your Unity game performance by exploring optimization techniques!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Game optimization is critical for delivering smooth and efficient gaming experiences - especially in larger-scale projects. In this course, you'll learn how to enhance game performance in Unity by leveraging analysis tools and applying advanced optimization techniques. This knowledge will enable you to craft fully-fledged games that run seamlessly no matter their complexity or size.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;An intermediate understanding of Unity is required for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize Unity’s Profiler effectively&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Analyze scenes with Frame Debugger&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement static and real-time lighting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply static batching techniques&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Optimize with Level of Detail (LOD)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master occlusion culling strategies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtoecsforunity6"&gt;&lt;a id="introtoecsforunity6" href="https://youtu.be/PJqOQYF71n4"&gt;Intro to ECS for Unity 6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Revolutionize your Unity projects with ECS!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Entity Component System (ECS) transforms game development in Unity by providing modern techniques to enhance performance and modularity. In this course, you'll explore the setup, usage, and benefits of ECS within Unity, enabling you to make complex projects with streamlined, efficient code. These skills will empower you to create games and apps that integrate high numbers of objects and calculations for large-scale projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;An intermediate understanding of Unity is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up ECS in Unity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create a massive ball spawner&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a basic player controller&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize multi-threading for performance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement modular programming concepts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand ECS structure&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildanarcadekartracinggameinunity"&gt;&lt;a id="buildanarcadekartracinggameinunity" href="https://youtu.be/U8MxxJ_GAhs"&gt;Build an Arcade Kart Racing Game in Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enhance your Unity game development skills by learning to create a 3D kart racing game. You'll explore a variety of robust techniques for creating car movement with Unity's new Input System - including adding physics for believable car movement, tracking kart position for win conditions, and more. Besides racing mechanics, you'll also learn how to turn your project into a split-screen local multiplayer game, giving you the foundations you need to expand in whatever direction you want to for racing-style games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up kart racing inputs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build a simple racing track&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Adjust kart movement with physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create systems for tracking race position&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control game flow with countdowns and win conditions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement split-screen multiplayer&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="constructamobilephysicsgameinunity"&gt;&lt;a id="constructamobilephysicsgameinunity" href="https://youtu.be/FtrsWEBa0og"&gt;Construct a Mobile Physics Game in Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Embrace the unique aspects of mobile touch gestures to build a physics-based Unity game. You'll explore various uses of gravity, drag, collisions, and more to create a game where players are slingshotted at enemies via dragging touch gestures. With the help of the Unity Device Simulator, you'll also learn how to tailor your project to various mobile devices - all skills which can be applied to other mobile and non-mobile game projects!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Simulate various mobile devices&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manipulate Unity's physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Code drag gestures to launch players&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Improve the camera with parallax&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up enemies and levels with collisions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create a mobile-friendly UI&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtoparticlesystemsforunitygames"&gt;&lt;a id="introtoparticlesystemsforunitygames" href="https://youtu.be/WZAyskU43fk"&gt;Intro to Particle Systems for Unity Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add new aesthetics to your game projects by mastering Unity's Particle System. You'll learn techniques for creating a variety of different particle effects to enhance the overall feel of your game - including sparks from fires, portals, and more. Regardless of the type of game you're aiming to make, these skills will provide you with the solid foundations needed to create unique visual experiences for your players to enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add particles to your scene&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Change particle shape and colors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control particle timings and amounts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manipulate particle animations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtogamedevelopmentwithgamemaker"&gt;&lt;a id="introtogamedevelopmentwithgamemaker" href="https://youtu.be/C6SNHyynROA"&gt;Intro to Game Development with GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn to create your own 2D games with GameMaker!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;GameMaker is one of the most popular engines available, featuring beginner-friendly architecture and cross-platform capabilities. In this course, you'll explore the fundamentals of working with GameMaker's tools while building a complete but simple game where the player must dodge an increasing number of projectiles to survive. These skills will provide you the foundations you need to start working with GameMaker in general and prepare you to build any sort of game you can imagine.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No prior experience is needed for this course!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with sprites, audio, &amp;amp; objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and design 2D levels&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement movement &amp;amp; collisions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand the eventing system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Code with GameMaker Language (GML)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add UI elements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createacomplete2dactionrpgingamemaker"&gt;&lt;a id="createacomplete2dactionrpgingamemaker" href="https://youtu.be/jy72ESN74k4"&gt;Create a Complete 2D Action RPG in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Craft a complete 2D Action RPG with GameMaker!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2D Action RPGs captivate players through their intricate combat mechanics and immersive worlds - making them a popular choice for both developers and gamers. In this course, you'll develop a feature-rich action RPG from start to finish with diverse mechanics such as enemy AI, player-controlled combat systems, and more. By the end of this course, you'll not only have a fully-fledged action RPG but also possess the skills to craft increasingly complex RPGs in GameMaker.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control player movement via keyboard&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement a robust inventory system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop engaging enemy AI behavior&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add particle effects, sounds, and animations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Craft a multi-weapon combat system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leverage tilesets for level design&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildareal-timestrategymini-gamewithgamemaker"&gt;&lt;a id="buildareal-timestrategymini-gamewithgamemaker" href="https://youtu.be/dvJIVYhaMjY"&gt;Build a Real-Time Strategy Mini-Game with GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Craft an immersive RTS mini-game using GameMaker!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Real-time strategy games captivate players with their dynamic gameplay and strategic depth, allowing them to control units and outmaneuver opponents in real time. In this course, you'll tackle core aspects of RTS games like enemy pathfinding and player controls while creating a fully functional, minimalistic strategy game. These skills will provide you not just the base to work with strategy games, but new ways to implement enemy AI for other genres.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of GameMaker and GML is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement efficient enemy pathfinding&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create maps using tilesets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop basic combat mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add immersive audio components&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhance visuals with particle effects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design intuitive game menus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="developanidleclickerfromscratchingamemaker"&gt;&lt;a id="developanidleclickerfromscratchingamemaker" href="https://youtu.be/TzRQNOKKSmU"&gt;Develop an Idle Clicker from Scratch in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create your own idle clicker game in GameMaker!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Idle clicker games are a popular and engaging genre, perfect for budding developers or those who want to focus on casual games. In this course, you'll create a rewarding idle clicker game from scratch using GameMaker - mastering common mechanics like auto-clickers that can be used across many projects. These skills will not just enable you to build idle clickers, but give you skills with sprites, particles, and more that can be applied in other genres.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of GameMaker and GML is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop core clicker game logic&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement an auto-clicker system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic sprites and backgrounds&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design a simple, functional main menu&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add particle effects for depth&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Integrate sound effects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeaminiturn-basedrpgfromscratchingamemaker"&gt;&lt;a id="makeaminiturn-basedrpgfromscratchingamemaker" href="https://youtu.be/Y9eyIg9jg94"&gt;Make a Mini Turn-Based RPG from Scratch in GameMaker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a mini turn-based RPG from scratch in GameMaker!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In today's rapidly evolving game market, turn-based RPGs stand out for their strategic depth and replay value. In this course, you'll master the art of creating a turn-based battle system reminiscent of old-school RPGs from start to finish using the GameMaker engine. These skills will set you on a path to crafting fully-fledged RPGs and give you hands-on experience crafting modular and complex combat.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of GameMaker and GML is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design a simple main menu&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage a turn-based battle system&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement multiple attack types&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modify character stats using inheritance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect win/loss conditions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create dynamic particle effects and SFX&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="comprehensiveintroductiontocprogramming"&gt;&lt;a id="comprehensiveintroductiontocprogramming" href="https://youtu.be/XIJ_JAR5FpM"&gt;The Comprehensive Introduction to C# Programming&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jumpstart your programming journey with the C# language!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Developed by Microsoft, C# is a versatile and robust language powering everything from simple applications to complex software systems. In this course, you'll dive deep into C# and explore foundational programming topics - all while cementing your learning with real-world examples and exercises. By the end, you'll have the foundational knowledge to excel in web development, mobile app creation, and even game development using major frameworks like Unity and MonoGame.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up a C# development environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand C# syntax and execution&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Process and manipulate data&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Store data - including with collections&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create efficient code with loops and methods&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply fundamentals to real-world examples&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildacompletemini2dgameenginewithc"&gt;&lt;a id="buildacompletemini2dgameenginewithc" href="https://youtu.be/X0jhC4vxyT0"&gt;Build a Complete Mini 2D Game Engine with C#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Construct a custom 2D game engine from scratch!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Creating your own 2D game engine gives you complete control and customization over your game development process, enabling you to tailor its features to fit project-specific needs. In this course, you'll build a comprehensive game engine using C#, mastering the fundamentals of game engines from rendering to input handling. These skills will not only enable you to make 2D games from complete scratch, but give you hands-on experience and opportunities to break boundaries in game design.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detect and react to user input&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Render visual elements with SFML&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage game objects and properties&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with physics using Aether Physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Transition seamlessly between game scenes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build a simple 2D game&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch"&gt;&lt;a id="learn3dmodelingwithblenderfromscratch" href="https://youtu.be/AC557GnNGqQ"&gt;Learn 3D Modeling with Blender from Scratch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master the foundations of Blender and 3D modeling!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3D modeling, the process of creating digital 3D objects, is a robust field of study with real-world applications for animation, game development, and more. In this course, you'll explore the free and open-source Blender software and learn the fundamental techniques for manipulating meshes and creating custom assets. These skills will form the basis for expanding your 3D modeling skills and open up opportunities to create unique assets for your projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No prior experience is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand how 3D objects work&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Move, rotate, and scale objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Edit vertices, edges, and faces&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with Blender's modifiers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply materials to meshes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Export models for other programs&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtoriggingmodelsinblender"&gt;&lt;a id="introtoriggingmodelsinblender" href="https://youtu.be/5XAwd7m3dkc"&gt;Intro to Rigging Models in Blender&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prepare your 3D models for animation by learning the fundamentals of rigging!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rigging is an important technique for 3D animation by which one creates a skeletal-like armature that can be manipulated to move parts of the 3D mesh around. You'll discover everything required for rigging - from setting up the ""bones"" to weight painting and controlling which parts of the mesh are affected by each bone. By the end, you'll have the foundations you'll need to master rigging any kind of 3D model and expand your skills in creating custom assets.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create bones to build an armature&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Connect your armature and 3D mesh&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control affected vertices with weight painting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Export rigged models&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply Mixamo animations to your models&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets"&gt;&lt;a id="magicavoxelforbeginners_createvoxelgameassets" href="https://youtu.be/jJDHSG20ZJQ"&gt;MagicaVoxel for Beginners - Create Voxel Game Assets&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Not an artist, but eager to create Minecraft-style voxel art models for your Unity games? Discover how to build your own 3D game models with MagicaVoxel - the free program that will enable you to build simple game models and environment. No experience in MagicaVoxel, 3D modeling or artistic experience is required - you will be shown how to use the essential tools from scratch, and how to export them into Unity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Topics included&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Using the different brushes and tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Camera controls to navigate your scene&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Creating a voxel art tree, a character and a lanscape&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Importing models into Unity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Working with color palettes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="promptengineeringforgamedevelopers"&gt;&lt;a id="promptengineeringforgamedevelopers" href="https://youtu.be/tFCZw14NGjc"&gt;Prompt Engineering for Game Developers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Revolutionize how you develop games with AI!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;AI is not just cutting-edge - it's a fundamental game changer for how game developers approach games. You'll explore how you can use AI to improve and enhance the game development process while fine-tuning your prompts to get the most out of AI. These techniques will vastly speed up your workflows and provide you new ways to change your games in unique ways.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ask AI for coding assistance&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate ideas with AI help&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Produce design documents&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create product pages with AI&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add AI-powered game mechanics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Alter prompts for desired outcomes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="exploreaudioforgodot4games"&gt;&lt;a id="exploreaudioforgodot4games" href="https://youtu.be/vT_km5EOGts"&gt;Explore Audio for Godot 4 Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Implement audio for your Godot games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Audio is an important facet of many game genres for creating atmosphere, immersion, and gameplay feedback. In this course, you'll dive into various ways you can implement audio in Godot as well as how to set up volume control settings for players. These skills will give you the foundations to add audio to any Godot game and enhance the overall game feel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Godot and GDScript is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add general background music&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement footsteps for player movement&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create the Doppler effect&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up reverb zones&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Separate audio tracks with buses&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop in-game volume controls&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="uvmappinginblenderforbeginners"&gt;&lt;a id="uvmappinginblenderforbeginners" href="https://youtu.be/bCMPqxpxZis"&gt;UV Mapping in Blender for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master texturing in Blender by learning how to use UV maps!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;UV mapping - a process by which you ""unwrap"" a 3D model into a flat surface - offers creators an easy way to paint complex textures and apply them to 3D models. You'll explore creating and applying UV maps to primitive objects, as well as complex.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Regardless of the sort of model you're making, skills in UV mapping will provide you with key skills to customize your 3D graphics to your exact specifications and allow you to go beyond flat colors for your textures.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply textures to an object&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create UV maps for primitive shapes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build models suitable for UV mapping&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Combine techniques to unwrap complex objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Export UV maps for 2D graphic's software&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paint textures onto a flattened UV map&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="uiuxforgamedesign"&gt;&lt;a id="uiuxforgamedesign" href="https://youtu.be/f0tBF6qfoMc"&gt;UI/UX for Game Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover UI and UX design principles for games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) play a critical role in communicating information to players and creating smooth, interactive gameplay. In this course, you'll build a UI/UX mockup for a mobile game while exploring design methodologies and wireframing techniques. These techniques will provide you new ways to approach UI/UX game design and to meaningfully apply iterative design to optimize your game's experience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No experience is needed to dive into this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand users with user stories&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create definitive design criteria&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize wireframes for mockups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply common design conventions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Test and iterate design choices&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Recognize design processes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $24.36 to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
