oshop"&gt;Intro to Pixel Art with Photoshop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#practicalpixelarttechniquesinphotoshop"&gt;Practical Pixel Art Techniques in Photoshop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#pixelartwithgimpforbeginners"&gt;Pixel Art with GIMP for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#createvectorgameartworkwithinkscape"&gt;Create Vector Game Artwork with Inkscape&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#leveldesignforbeginners"&gt;Level Design for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#explorestorytellingforgames"&gt;Explore Storytelling for Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $22.21 to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="0"&gt;Pay $1 to unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtogamedesign"&gt;&lt;a id="introtogamedesign" href="https://youtu.be/FdhFX3SCVOc"&gt;Intro to Game Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover how the core concepts of game design can help you to create fun and intuitive games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Game design is a fundamental process needed when creating any game - from the smallest platformer to the largest MMORPG. In this course, you'll start mastering the foundations of game design by examining each core component and how they apply to real-world games. By the end, you'll understand both why game design is important and, more crucially, how to apply the concepts to your own games and create a stunning portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Plan a game around a core mechanic or experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Engage players by providing tangible goals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Structure game actions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide players through the game&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand game feel and its effects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Show players how to play in different ways&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeafully-fledged2dactionrpgindefold"&gt;&lt;a id="makeafully-fledged2dactionrpgindefold" href="https://youtu.be/0E45JyYMui0"&gt;Make a Fully-Fledged 2D Action RPG in Defold&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build your own 2D action RPG from start to finish in Defold!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Action RPGs remain a cornerstone genre in game development, challenging creators to bring together exciting combat and immersive systems. In this course, you’ll create a top-down action RPG project where the player must survive and shoot a barrage of randomly spawned enemies. These skills will empower you to tackle more advanced game mechanics in Defold, and serve as the perfect springboard to designing your games with action-based gameplay in mind.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement player movement and controls&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create a dynamic camera with boundaries&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build simple enemy AI behaviors&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add health bars that follow entities&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Structure levels with scenes and menus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spawn enemies and projectiles in-game&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="learngamedevelopmentwithdefoldfromscratch"&gt;&lt;a id="learngamedevelopmentwithdefoldfromscratch" href="https://youtu.be/sT4NN9XoYSE"&gt;Learn Game Development with Defold from Scratch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master Defold - a free and powerful game engine for building 2D &amp;amp; 3D games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Defold is a rising star in game development, providing developers a quick and easy way to build games for PC, mobile, and consoles with a single project. Through this course, you'll explore the foundations of the Defold game engine from start to finish - including how to work with Lua scripting to program your game logic. These skills will give you the building blocks for developing your dream games with Defold and set you up for success in other genres.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate the Defold engine&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manipulate sprites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with player input&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Script with Lua fundamentals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand the game camera&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Combine skills in a mini-project&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="makeafarmingrpgfromscratchwithdefold"&gt;&lt;a id="makeafarmingrpgfromscratchwithdefold" href="https://youtu.be/5HuLbF5N_iA"&gt;Make a Farming RPG from Scratch with Defold&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Build a farming RPG from start to finish in Defold!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Farming RPGs are incredibly engaging projects that blend different genre game mechanics with the joy of creation and management. In this course, you’ll develop a farming RPG while focusing on implementing core gameplay features such as crop farming, day progression, and player controls. These hands-on skills will enable you to create more complex and ambitious projects in the future and teach you advanced methodologies for working with sprites.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Defold and Lua is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up a player controller&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and manage crop systems&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement day progression&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with sprite atlases&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize techniques for data management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design interactive UI elements&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="buildacomplete2dplatformerindefold"&gt;&lt;a id="buildacomplete2dplatformerindefold" href="https://youtu.be/_fu8zADXegA"&gt;Build a Complete 2D Platformer in Defold&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create your own 2D platformer game with Defold!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Platformers are not only an ever-enduring genre, but a great choice for developers looking to make their first fully-fledged game. In this course, you’ll build a complete platformer game from start to finish with multiple levels, enemies, and collectables. These skills will expand your knowledge of Defold and Lua and teach you essential mechanics that can be used for your own platformer projects - as well as other genres!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A basic understanding of Defold and Lua is needed for this course.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create and manage tilemaps&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Design player controllers with animations&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement coin collectables&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customize enemy behavior&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add sound effects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manage gameplay flow&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;… and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="createablockbreakergameindefold"&gt;&lt;a id="createablockbreakergameindefold" href="https://youtu.be/a732-y4Ppsc"&gt;Create a Block Breaker Game in Defold&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover physics-based game mechanics by building a block breaker game in Defold!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Block breaker games have stood the test of time, blending arcade action with physics-based mechanics for challenging gameplay. In this course, you'll create a fully-fledged block breaker game featuring a paddle, bouncing ball, and procedurally generated blocks, all powered by scripting for automated layout customization. These skills will help you upgrade your knowledge of physics, math, and more - all while preparing you for even more sophisticated 2D titles in Defold.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You'll learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Implement vector math for ball physics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Structure levels procedurally&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Control object movement with a mouse&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop block-breaking gameplay logic&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Customize game visuals with scripting&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Add polish with UI and sound&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="introtopixelartwithphotoshop"&gt;&lt;a id="introtopixelartwithphotoshop" href="https://youtu.be/ykqeL_O93hY"&gt;Intro to Pixel Art with Photoshop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create your own pixel art assets from scratch using Photoshop!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pixel art has been a popular art style since the very first video games - and remains popular for modern games as well. By exploring key features offered by Photoshop, you'll master fundamental techniques for creating pixel art characters, spritesheets, animation sheets, and more. The skills learned here with Photoshop can be adapted in numerous ways to suit your needs - no matter what kind of pixel art game you're making.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use Photoshop's pencil and eraser tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhance productivity with layers and swatches&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up spritesheets with multiple tile sprites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paint pixel art characters and backgrounds&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Make sheets for sprite animation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Export art files for future use&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="practicalpixelarttechniquesinphotoshop"&gt;&lt;a id="practicalpixelarttechniquesinphotoshop" href="https://youtu.be/ez82g2BRQ4M"&gt;Practical Pixel Art Techniques in Photoshop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Master a variety of useful pixel art techniques for custom assets!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pixel art remains a steadfast art style to use in games, and is particularly popular in the indie sector. In this Photoshop course, you'll explore shading, color palettes, animation sprites, different materials &amp;amp; objects, and more - all while practically applying them to several projects. By the end, you'll have learned several key techniques for customizing your 2D project's aesthetics with pixel art.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This course assumes basic familiarity with Photoshop.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Select and apply character color palettes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deal with walk cycle animation sprites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mimic motion blur with trails&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Craft tilemap-ready tilesets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Shade different organic materials&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Apply material-appropriate highlights to metallic objects&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="pixelartwithgimpforbeginners"&gt;&lt;a id="pixelartwithgimpforbeginners" href="https://youtu.be/aBB01DaK7-g"&gt;Pixel Art with GIMP for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;GIMP - the free and highly versatile image editing program. From basic asset design steps such as shading and color selection, to character design and dynamic poses, you'll be creating high-quality games and assets. With assets that can be imported into many other programs (such as Unity and Phaser), you'll gain skills that will enable you to give your games a modern and professional look.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Set up the pencil, eraser, and visibility Grid in GIMP&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create basic monster forms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Build a Mario-like character&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop and assemble terrain tiles and sets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot common issues faced by artists and asset designers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="createvectorgameartworkwithinkscape"&gt;&lt;a id="createvectorgameartworkwithinkscape" href="https://youtu.be/J1mlXkdLBAI"&gt;Create Vector Game Artwork with Inkscape&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create stunning, high-quality, scalable graphics and art using Inkscape - the professional, open source graphics editor. With no prior experience in drawing or with Inkscape required, you'll learn how to use Inkscape to its maximum potential, and design high-definition, flexible graphics that will bring life and color to your existing games, applications and projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create foreground, background and character graphics&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use vector graphics, and learn their advantages over typical bitmaps&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Employ graphic object types and attributes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Utilize color manipulation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand and build tilesets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;... and more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="leveldesignforbeginners"&gt;&lt;a id="leveldesignforbeginners" href="https://youtu.be/82Y8b9PnK2Y"&gt;Level Design for Beginners&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enhance your game project's levels by diving into the expansive topic of level design. Studying professionally published video games, you'll learn new techniques for creating engaging and intuitive levels that subtly guide the player through the game, enhance the storytelling, and cater to specific needs of a genre. You'll get to explore both a variety of ways in which levels can be created with a robust workflow, and develop concrete skills to make purposeful, battle-tested design choices to provide players with fun game experiences.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide players using lighting, landmarks, and more&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Teach players how to play with level design choices&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Enhance storytelling with the environment&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Adjust designs for open world and multiplayer games&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Follow basic level design workflows&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3 id="explorestorytellingforgames"&gt;&lt;a id="explorestorytellingforgames" href="https://youtu.be/s3VT2g0_LCI"&gt;Explore Storytelling for Games&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discover tips and techniques for designing game narratives! You'll learn by studying real games, and master a variety of methods for telling stories through characters, plots, mechanics, and more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No matter what type of games you want to build, the skills you'll learn will help to make your games more immersive and engaging for your players.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will learn how to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Understand technical story design&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Create compelling protagonists &amp;amp; antagonists&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Base your story on a three-act structure&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use game-based methods to convey your story&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Incorporate interactive, choice-based storytelling&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Advance the story with quests&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="bta1"&gt;Pay more than the average of $22.21 to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
